<title>Bahraini political prisoner</title>
<content type="html" xml:lang="en">&lt;p&gt;Stallman Sez: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; A Bahraini political prisoner has been &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/feb/21/us-seriously-concerned-over-jailing-of-bahraini-activist-nabeel-rajab&#34;&gt;sentenced to more years in prison&lt;/a&gt; for saying that Bahrain tortures political prisoners, and for insulting &lt;a href=&#34;/glossary.html#salafi&#34;&gt;Salafi Arabia&lt;/a&gt; by criticizing its air campaign against Yemen. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; He&amp;#39;s surely right in criticizing that.  As for the torture, if he says Bahrain uses torture he surely knows. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; For either of those statements to be a crime is in itself sufficient to conclude that Bahrain is a repressive, evil state — if we didn&amp;#39;t &lt;a href=&#34;https://stallman.org/archives/2016-nov-feb.html#16_November_2016_(Repression_in_Bahrain)&#34;&gt;already know that&lt;/a&gt;.   &lt;/p&gt;</content>
