<title>Student protests</title>
<content type="html" xml:lang="en">&lt;p&gt;Stallman Sez: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Florida high school students &lt;a href=&#34;Https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/feb/21/florida-students-confront-lawmakers-on-gun-control-as-thousands-walk-out&#34;&gt;went to the state capitol&lt;/a&gt; to demand gun control.  Thousands of students left school to protest. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; The school superintendent of Needville, Texas, declared he would &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.dailykos.com/story/2018/2/21/1743418/-Texas-school-district-threatens-suspension-if-students-protest-to-prevent-the-next-mass-shooting&#34;&gt;suspend any students&lt;/a&gt; that walk out of school to protest. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; I hope all the high school students in that district walk out to protest at his office, to show they are not going to be intimidated. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; If he follows through with the threat to &amp;quot;suspend&amp;quot; them, they can organize a three-day teach-in, where they will learn things that are more important than what is normally taught in school.   &lt;/p&gt;</content>
<category term="stallman"/>
<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://localhost:8000/post/01C77PHC00BEDCFWGEBESQ41ZY.html"/>
