<title>Purpose of education</title>
<content type="html" xml:lang="en">&lt;p&gt;Stallman Sez: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Measuring education in terms of increased income afterwards is &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.commondreams.org/views/2018/02/20/economists-dont-know-crap-about-education&#34;&gt;missing the main point&lt;/a&gt; of education. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; We used to acknowledge clearly that the purpose of education was to prepare people to be capable citizens of a democracy.  The mere attempt to judge issues of education in narrow economic terms indicates a basic error.   &lt;/p&gt;</content>
<category term="stallman"/>
<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://localhost:8000/post/01C77PHC009G9ZM28GBJDNP39J.html"/>
