<published>2018-02-25T00:00:00.000Z</published>
<updated>2018-02-25T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
<title>Media and war crimes</title>
<content type="html" xml:lang="en">&lt;p&gt;Stallman Sez: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.commondreams.org/views/2018/02/16/us-stumbled-torture-says-nyt-reporter&#34;&gt;An analyzed example&lt;/a&gt; of how the mainstream media legitimize US war crimes: the New York Times said that the US &amp;quot;stumbled into torture&amp;quot; and that drone attacks that kill civilians merely &amp;quot;go wrong&amp;quot;. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;/glossary.html#dubya&#34;&gt;Dubya&lt;/a&gt; pushed hard for use of torture, including finding subordinates to &lt;a href=&#34;https://stallman.org/archives/2005-sep-dec.html#16%20December%202005%20(Torture)&#34;&gt;create legalistic excuses&lt;/a&gt; for it. As for the drone attacks, the US &lt;a href=&#34;https://stallman.org/archives/2012-nov-feb.html#28_December_2012_(US_drone_strikes_that_killed_civilians)&#34;&gt;resists acknowledging&lt;/a&gt; that they kill civilians.   &lt;/p&gt;</content>
<category term="stallman"/>
<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://localhost:8000/post/01C7544N00T8XSM6H3CJQDPC7G.html"/>
